UNIVERSAL PROPERTY & CASUALTY INSURANCE COMPANY, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
William M. KENNA and Cynthia L. Kenna, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-3499 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. January 22, 2019

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

Petitioner's notice of voluntary dismissal is accepted and this petition for writ of certiorari is dismissed.

The court accepts the parties' stipulation that respondents' motion for appellate attorneys' fees is withdrawn.
